            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#k">Colors of the Stars.</hi>
                </head>
                <p>&#x2014;The Grecian astronomers<lb break="yes"/>knew only red stars; while, by the aid of the teles-<lb break="no"/>cope, the moderns have discovered in the starry vault,<lb break="yes"/>in the celestial fields which light traverses, as in the<lb break="yes"/>corollas of our flowering plants, and in the metallic<lb break="yes"/>oxides, almost every gradation of prismatic color be-<lb break="no"/>tween the two extremes of refrangibility, or between<lb break="yes"/>the violet and the red rays.&#x2014;<hi rendition="#i" >Humboldt.</hi>
                </p>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
        </body>
